    "summary": "With his broad civil engineering knowledge & experience, Mr. Arnold provides consultancy services in the field of hydraulics (water levels & waves) and the design of hydraulic structures (flood defences, bed & bank protection, navigation locks and pumping stations). He is involved as consultant in modelling studies, risk & safety assessments and the design of flood defenses and several environmental impact studies. He gained experience in projects in the Netherlands and abroad, comprising the restoration and rehabilitation of the New Orleans flood defence system in the wake of Hurricane Katrina, design work for the third set of locks of the Panama Canal and the dike safety & risk assessment Aqua Blanca Dike along the Cauca River in Colombia. Recently he has worked in Colombia for three years on the rehabilitation of the Canal del Dique system (design of two navigation locks and a weir). \n\nSpecialties: design of hydraulic structures, risk & safety assessments of flood defences, environmental impact studies, project management",
